You have to be either a student or a fairly recent alum. I want to be able to check that you have solid mastery of the material that you're offering to tutor (grades of B and above).

If you don't have a berkeley.edu address, we may have to work through the questions by e-mail.

Heather
hello, do I have to be a student in order to be considered as a private tutor?

history.content:
Hello Everyone,

I've been asked to make a new list of private tutors for Summer 2020. Of course things will be somewhat different than in previous semesters, but perhaps this is a way that you could provide some service to your fellow students who are having a hard time with online instruction. The form to apply to be a private tutor is here, or if you have signed up before, you can ask me to move your entry and just tell me what you'd like to change. 

Warm regards,

Heather
